    "How do we design assignments and assessments where the boundaries between human and AI writing are moot?",
    "That is, when, if ever, are we going to get to the postplagiarism world that Eaton (2021; 2023) envisions?",
    "Until we reach those tranquil waters, we will have to confront the issue of academic integrity in imaginative ways.",
    "Just as in the past with contract cheating, for instance, GenAI blurs, if not crosses, the line between what is original, individual work and what is conceived as assistance, if not overt plagiarism.",
    "Gray (2022) stated that the contract cheating industry encompasses \"a devaluing and de-prioritization of original work when it comes to the classroom space, predatory relationships between consumers and service providers, and a cavalier approach to handling data privacy \" (p. 190)."
